<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-06-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-06-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="529" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d529">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">812.00/22826: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Consul at Ciudad Juarez</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Dow</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-06-18"><hi rend="italic">June 18,
                                        1919</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p>Your June 17, 9 p.m.<note n="49" xml:id="d529fn49"><hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_559">p. 559</ref>.</note></p>
                            <p>Urgently renew your request that adequate force of troops be sent to
                                Casas Grandes district for protection Mormon colonies and advise <pb facs="0656" n="571" xml:id="pg_571"/> Department whether these
                                colonies are in any immediate danger from attacks by Villistas.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>